{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17614195","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17614195"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T14:42:20+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T14:42:20+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16348"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"16348","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/16348"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9039"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80939"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"9039","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/9039"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16348"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"66268"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"8"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"1992"},{"type":"tags","id":"4930"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"},{"type":"tags","id":"5586"},{"type":"tags","id":"7507"},{"type":"tags","id":"9829"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"21498"},{"type":"contributions","id":"27699"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80939","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/80939"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EThe orbit contains several important venous drainage pathways that connect to different intracranial and extracranial venous systems. One of these veins drains to the pterygoid plexus via the inferior orbital fissure.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is this vein?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Superior ophthalmic vein","Central retinal vein","Conjunctival vein","Inferior ophthalmic vein","Episcleral vein"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Einferior ophthalmic vein\u003C/strong\u003E drains the lower portion of the orbit and passes through the inferior orbital fissure to reach the pterygoid plexus in the infratemporal fossa.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Esuperior ophthalmic vein\u003C/strong\u003E drains to the cavernous sinus via the superior orbital fissure. The \u003Cstrong\u003Ecentral retinal vein\u003C/strong\u003E drains into the superior ophthalmic vein. The \u003Cstrong\u003Econjunctival veins\u003C/strong\u003E and \u003Cstrong\u003Eepiscleral veins\u003C/strong\u003E are smaller vessels that drain into the ophthalmic veins.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThis venous drainage pattern is clinically significant because it provides potential routes for infection to spread between the face, orbit, and intracranial structures.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The inferior ophthalmic vein drains the lower part of the orbit and passes through the inferior orbital fissure to reach the pterygoid plexus.","The superior ophthalmic vein drains to the cavernous sinus via the superior orbital fissure, not the pterygoid plexus."],"references":["Michael-Titus, A. T., \u0026 Shortland, P. (2022). The Nervous System, E-Book: The Nervous System, E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Bird B, Stawicki SP. Anatomy, Head and Neck, Ophthalmic Arteries. 2023 Aug 8. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan\u2013. PMID: 29493942","Probst, L., \u0026 Tsai, J. (2024). Ophthalmology: Clinical and Surgical Principles. CRC Press","Salmon, J. F. (2024). Kanski\u0027s Clinical Ophthalmology E-Book: A Systematic Approach. Elsevier Health Sciences","Kels BD, Grzybowski A, Grant-Kels JM. Human ocular anatomy. Clin Dermatol. 2015 Mar-Apr;33(2):140-6. doi: 10.1016/j.clindermatol.2014.10.006. PMID: 25704934"]},"